column3: select  e.idcase, (strftime('%s',e1.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e. timestamp)) from event_log e inner join event_log e1 on e1.idcase = e.idcase and e1.timestamp > e.timestamp where e.activity = 'Permit submitted by employee' and e1.activity = 'Permit approved by administration'

column2: SELECT e.idcase, strftime('%s', a.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.timestamp) as 'Permit approval time' FROM event_log e JOIN event_log a ON e.idcase = a.idcase WHERE e.activity = 'Employee requesting permit' AND a.activity = 'Permit approved by administration'
column3: select  e.idcase, (strftime('%s',e1.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e. timestamp)) from event_log e inner join event_log e1 on e1.idcase = e.idcase and e1.timestamp > e.timestamp where e.activity = 'Permit submitted by employee' and e1.activity = 'Permit approved by administration'

column2: SELECT idcase FROM event_log GROUP BY idcase HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT activity) < COUNT(activity)
column3: SELECT DISTINCT idcase FROM event_log GROUP BY idcase, activity HAVING COUNT(*) > 1

column2: SELECT idcase FROM event_log WHERE idcase IN ( SELECT idcase FROM ( SELECT idcase, activity, LEAD(activity) OVER (PARTITION BY idcase ORDER BY timestamp) AS next_activity FROM event_log ) WHERE activity = next_activity )
